      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must have documented QA plan, version control, regression test suite, and independent code review at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Version control and regression testing are in place, but independent third-party code review has not been completed and the QA plan lacks traceability to individual test cases. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions or equivalent formal verification demonstrating observed order of accuracy matches theoretical order for all governing equations.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark verification problems were solved and convergence was demonstrated, but method of manufactured solutions has not been applied to the hemolysis transport equation. Theoretical order of accuracy is unconfirmed. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent on at least three systematically refined grids; GCI reported for hemolysis QOI at all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level grid refinement study performed and GCI computed for primary flow quantities. GCI for the hemolysis index QOI specifically was computed at only two of five operating points; remaining three are extrapolated. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must replicate VAD operating envelope (flow rate, rotational speed, hematocrit, temperature) with documented measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments were conducted at nominal conditions but hematocrit and temperature were not controlled to VAD-representative values. Measurement uncertainty for hemolysis index is reported only as a single pooled estimate rather than per-condition. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., ASME V&V 20 validation metric or equivalent) applied to hemolysis QOI with experimental uncertainty bounds explicitly included in pass/fail criterion.",
      "rationale": "Predicted and measured hemolysis index values are compared graphically and mean absolute error is reported. No formal validation metric incorporating experimental uncertainty intervals is applied. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QOI used in validation (hemolysis index) must be directly the same metric used in the regulatory acceptance criterion with no surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the regulatory QOI. Validation data use a modified hemolysis index (MIH) with a different normalization convention. A conversion factor is applied but its uncertainty propagation into the acceptance criterion is not quantified. Achieved level 2 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must span the full VAD operating envelope defined in the COU; extrapolation beyond validated range must be quantified and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments cover three of the five required flow-speed combinations. Two operating points lie outside the validated range and are addressed by extrapolation without explicit uncertainty bounding. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, round-off, and solver residual errors must be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error for the hemolysis QOI.",
      "rationale": "Residual convergence plots are provided but no formal decomposition of solver error from discretization error has been performed for the hemolysis transport equation. This factor is flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with independent analyst review; checklist-based verification of boundary condition setup and post-processing steps.",
      "rationale": "No independent analyst review of simulation setup or post-processing has been performed. Use error is identified as an epistemic gap; no evidence of workflow checklists or peer review of model inputs. Achieved level 1 against required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic evaluation of hemolysis constitutive model form uncertainty including comparison of at least two physically distinct model forms against experimental data.",
      "rationale": "Only the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is used. No alternative model form (e.g., strain-based or mechanistic red cell damage models) has been evaluated. Model form uncertainty is an unquantified epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Full probabilistic characterization of all model inputs with sensitivity analysis identifying dominant contributors to hemolysis QOI uncertainty; Monte Carlo propagation with at least 1000 samples.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on geometric tolerances and inlet flow rate. Blood viscosity, hematocrit, and hemolysis model coefficients were treated as deterministic. Dominant uncertainty contributors to the hemolysis QOI have not been identified. Achieved level 1 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size sufficient to characterize biological variability in hemolysis measurements; statistical power analysis documented.",
      "rationale": "Sample size and biological variability in the FDA pump hemolysis experiments are not reported in available documentation. No statistical power analysis has been performed. This is an epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented mapping between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters; any differences quantified and their impact on QOI bounded.",
      "rationale": "The mapping between FDA generic pump experimental inputs and the specific VAD COU inputs (patient-specific flow conditions, implant geometry tolerances) has not been formally documented. Input equivalency is an unresolved epistemic gap. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    }
